doc.after: In July 2014, there were 68 DC-10s and MD-10s in airline service with operators FedEx Express (60), Kelowna Flightcraft Air Charter (4), and others with fewer aircraft.[38] The aging models are now largely used as dedicated freight aircraft. "The DC-10 is going to be remembered as a better cargo plane than passenger plane," said Richard Aboulafia, an analyst with the Teal Group.[39]
